    <div class="problem-body">
      <p>Every week there's a new model, a new framework, a new capability being called a game-changer. Some of it is. Most of it needs context before you know how to respond. The signal-to-noise ratio is rough right now.</p>
      <p>I've spent over 14 years in roles where I had to know the difference — advising organizations at Gartner, supporting the fastest-scaling AI startups at AWS, and building products myself. I've specialized in AI over the last 8 years and I've seen what works in production and what looks good in a demo.</p>
      <p>Operator's Log is my attempt to share that perspective. Not the loudest take. Not a vendor pitch. Just honest, grounded observations from someone who's been accountable for real AI outcomes — and is still in the middle of it.</p>
      <p>If you're making real decisions about AI — for your team, your product, or your career — I hope it's useful.<br /><br />-Jason</p>
